Through the four informal evaluations we found out that the tree metaphor were a understood by users while they got different interpretations of it according to their own life states. \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
On the other hand we observed that users were not comfortable to interact with the low-fi prototype as it looked so undeveloped. \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The limited functioned prototype was sufficient enough to valid our concept, while a video prototype might be more suitable so that users won\'92t be afraid to break the prototype.\
3.2 Hi-fi Prototype and Testing\
Photoshop and Invision App were used to design a hi-fi interface and an App-like interactive prototype that could run on iPhones. With the hi-fi prototype, tow rounds of cooperative evaluations were carried out with two secretaries representing our primary users and two Master students representing our secondary users. The participants were asked to first explore the application and think aloud, their preference of the . And then a scenario and several tasks were given to the them to identify problems in usability and information structures. After one round of testing, we made changes on the interface accordingly and validate our changes in the second round of testing. Each testing ended with a debriefing interview.\
